<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI MAYOR PRESIDES OVER HANDOVER CEREMONY FOR DEPARTMENT
CHIEFS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb.  1 (CNA) 02/01/07  19:17:37 (By Elisa Kao)
</P>
<P>
Taipei Mayor Hau Lung-bin presided over a hand over ceremony for
several department chiefs Thursday, urging the new members of his
working team to offer their best services to the citizens through
interdepartment cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Taipei city government will see five new department chiefs,
including Department of Finance Director Lin Chien-yuan,  Fire
Department  Commissioner Hsiung  Kwang-hua,  Feitsui  Reservoir
Administration Director-General Lee Kung- che, Research,
Development and Evaluation Commission Chairman Sheng Chih-jen,
and Department of Personnel Director Han Chun-ying.
</P>
<P>
Noting that these new section chiefs are all elite persons in
their respective spheres of work, Hau said their arrivals will
complete the Taipei city government working team.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the handover ceremony on behalf of other new section
chiefs, Sheng said although individual performance is important,
he would like to focus on team work in the future to help Hau
implement his policies.
</P>
<P>
Hau re hired the outgoing Department of Personnel Director Chung
Yu-nan as city government adviser for his extraordinary
performance in streamlining personnel and planning English
training programs for the city government employees.
</P>
<P>
According to Yen Chiu-lai, deputy minister of Cabinet-level
Central Personnel Administration (CPA), who witnessed the
handover ceremony, the CPA has rewarded Chung for his efforts in
promoting the privatization of public buses and gender equality,
employing aboriginal persons, and saving money for the Taipei
city government.
</P>
